<COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">Falcon Holding Group Inc.</COREF> said <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">it</COREF> agreed to acquire <COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">about 54,000 subscribers</COREF> from First Carolina Cable TV Limited Partnership for about $ 100 million , or roughly $ 2,000 a subscriber .
<COREF ID="0" TYPE="IDENT">The subscribers</COREF> are in 52 different communities in Georgia , Alabama and Mississippi .
Completion of the sale is expected early next year , <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">Falcon</COREF> said .
Currently , <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">Falcon</COREF> has about 750,000 cable - television subscribers around the nation ; <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">the company 's</COREF> cable - television unit reported 1988 revenue of about $ 100 million .
In composite trading on the American Stock Exchange , <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">Falcon</COREF> closed at $ 20 , unchanged .
